Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Clay fine buff-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '722'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 17. Name Tharsagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0365.22.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0576)
